ic Flair]] vs. [[Sting (wrestler)|Sting]]\n|}\n\n===1990===\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable succession-box\" style=\"font-size:85%;\"\n! width=8%| Date\n! width=14%| Event\n! width=14%| Venue\n! width=14%| Location\n! width=50%| Main event\n|-\n\n|February 25\n|[[WrestleWar (1990)|WrestleWar]]\n|[[Greensboro Coliseum]]\n|[[Greensboro, North Carolina]]\n|[[Ric Flair]] vs. [[Lex Luger]]\n|-\n|May 19\n|[[Capital Combat]]\n|[[D.C. Armory]]\n|[[Washington, D.C.]]\n|[[Ric Flair]] vs. [[Lex Luger]]\n|-\n|July 7\n|[[The Great American Bash (1990)|The Great American Bash]]\n|[[Baltimore Arena]]\n|[[Baltimore]]\n|[[Ric Flair]] vs. [[Sting (wrestler)|Sting]]\n|-\n|October 27\n|[[Halloween Havoc (1990)|Halloween Havoc]]\n|[[UIC Pavilion]]\n|[[Chicago]]\n|[[Sting (wrestler)|Sting]] vs. [[Sid Vicious (wrestler)|Sid Vicious]]\n|-\n|December 16\n|[[Starrcade (1990)|Starrcade]]<ref name=\"Starrcade\">The first wrestling pay-per-view event under the World Championship Wrestling (WCW) banner and the last wrestling pay-per-view event under the National Wrestling Alliance (NWA) banner.</ref>\n|[[Kiel Auditorium]]\n|[[St. Louis|St. Louis, Missouri]]\n|[[Sting (wrestler)|Sting]] vs. [[Ric Flair|The Black Scorpion]]\n|}\n\n==WCW pay-per-view events==\n===1991===\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable succession-box\" style=\"font-size:85%;\"\n! width=8%| Date\n! width=14%| Event\n! width=14%| Venue\n! width=14%| Location\n! width=50%| Main event\n|-\n\n| February 24 || [[WrestleWar (1991)|WrestleWar]] || [[Arizona Veterans Memorial Coliseum]] || [[Phoenix, Arizona]] || [[Larry Zbyszko]] and [[The Four Horsemen (professional wrestling)|The Four Horsemen]] ([[Barry Windham]], [[Ric Flair]] and [[Sid Eudy|Sid Vicious]]) vs. [[Brian Pillman]], [[Sting (wrestler)|Sting]] and [[The Steiner Brothers]] ([[Rick Steiner]] and [[Scott Steiner]])\n|-\n| March 21 (aired April) || [[WCW/New Japan Supershow I|Japan Supershow I]] || [[Tokyo Dome]] || [[Tokyo, Japan]] || [[Tatsumi Fujinami]] vs. [[Ric Flair]]\n|-\n